## Debugging

- When logging variables, prefer the concise, extendable style `console.log({ foo })`
- If variables need to be renamed for clarity or for properties, still use an object. Example: `console.log({ 'foo.bar': foo.bar })`
- Do no use the style `console.log("foo", foo)`

## Edge-case handling

Follow the advice of "left-align the happy path." This means that if there is an edge-case, an error-case, or anything else invalid, handle that first in a conditional block if appropriate before moving on to the happy path case, which is indented in a block. Since it's not indented in the block it's "left-aligned." Examples:

Do this:

```ts
function reverseString(input: string) {
  if (!input) {
    throw new Error("No input found");
  }

  return input.split("").reverse().join("");
}
```

Don't do this

```ts
function reverseString(input: string) {
  if (input) {
    return input.split("").reverse().join("");
  } else {
    throw new Error("No input found");
  }
}
```
